title: Grateful Dead Live at Capitol Theater on 1971-02-21
lineage: CD -> Samplitude Professional v10.02 -> Adobe Audition v1.5 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, Me And Bobby McGee, Loser, Easy Wind, Playin' In The Band, Bertha, Me & My Uncle, Ripple, Next Time You See Me, Sugar Magnolia, Greatest Story Ever Told-> Johnny B. Goode

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Bird Song, Cumberland Blues, I'm A King Bee, Beat It On Down The Line, Wharf Rat, Truckin', Casey Jones, Good Lovin'-> Drums-> Good Lovin'-> Uncle John's Band

E.S.P. show - Other artist(s): NRPS

reviews.review_text: Fantastic Best recording of this show in my opinion.
one show down and another to go... 2nd that emotion,sounds Grate!
Review I like the 2nd set.  It begins with Weir asking the crowd to howl like a coyote and then it goes into a really good China Cat-I Know You Rider.

Ron "Pigpen" McKernan An infamous Pigpen screwup before the jam in Easy Wind. For the rest of the song, they're just going through the motions, probably pissed. Still, a good show, before they began their downhill slide 15 months later (which I partly attribute to Ron's absence).
Not the best of the run Not the strongest show of this run at the Capitol but still a great listen. The second set is strong with a nice China Rider opener.
thanks Thanks for not breaking up Good Lovin'!
Good Lovin' The second set is excellent and there's Ripple.

Funky Good Lovin' Nice version here. Not a ton in the way of jamming, but the boys lock in on a groove and churn away hotly under Pig's rap.

Overall a pretty good show, but not nearly as strong as the 18th-20th.
- Not bad. A lot of the songs are new and still rough, and the jams aren't that great.
